Package org.aksw.deer.parameter

Interface ParametrizedPlugin

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    EnrichmentOperator
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractEnrichmentOperator, AuthorityConformationEnrichmentOperator, CloneEnrichmentOperator, DereferencingEnrichmentOperator, FilterEnrichmentOperator, GeoFusionEnrichmentOperator, LinkingEnrichmentOperator, MergeEnrichmentOperator, NEREnrichmentOperator, ParameterlessEnrichmentOperator, PredicateConformationEnrichmentOperator

    public interface ParametrizedPlugin
    Base interface for parametrized plugins, defines a contract.

    A ParametrizedPlugin is a class that is parametrized using a ParameterMap.
    It should only be instantiated from instances of ParametrizedPluginFactory. For this to work, each plugin type needs to define a plugin type interface that extends at least ParametrizedPlugin and ExtensionPoint. Furthermore, each non-abstract class implementing a plugin type interface should be annotated with Extension.
